title: Ask HN: Does HN cause more FOMO than Twitter and YT?
text:
With some restraint on IG, YouTube and Twitter, you can limit your content to topics/creators you are interested.

All these social media serve different purposes. But HN is too broad. So might be more dopamine and FOMO and therefore distraction than Twitter and YT.

Ask HN: Code libary design for GPT AI systems?
text:
I have seen other posts where they predict GPT-4 will be able to write code and then rewrite that code to make corrections.

If you were going to make a code library that a GPT-4 like system could use in writing code, what features and aspects would you consider to make it easier for the AI to use?
